## Multi-tenancy rules (non-negotiable)
> Obey `../standards-kb/01-architecture-multitenancy.md` in full. Summary:
- Every tenant-scoped table has a `[TENANT_ID_COLUMN]` column.
- Tenant isolation is enforced by **[ISOLATION_MECHANISM]**, not just app code.
- No query may run without a tenant context set. A missing tenant context is an **error**, never "return all".
- [SUB_TENANT_SCOPE — e.g. branch/center scoping (`branchId`) sits *inside* a tenant.]

## Coding conventions
- [CODE_ORGANIZATION — e.g. feature-first folders, grouped by domain module, not by layer].
- Every mutation of [SIGNIFICANT_DATA] writes an **audit-log** entry.
- Errors: typed, never swallowed. No `[FORBIDDEN_TYPE, e.g. any]`. No stray debug logging in committed code.
- Tests co-located; every [CRITICAL_LOGIC_UNIT — e.g. state-machine transition] has a test.
- Follow the MUST/SHOULD rules in `../standards-kb/` for all NFRs, and `../design-system-kb/` for all UI.

## How work is scoped
- The unit of work is **one module or one screen** — never "the app".
- Build order follows the priority signals in `knowledge-base/REQUIREMENTS-DIGEST-AND-GAPS.md`.
- Each slice: Spec → Plan → Build → Verify → Review. Each PR meets `DEFINITION-OF-DONE.md`.

## Autonomy contract (how the AI should behave)
- **Build autonomously; the user reviews git diffs.** Do not stop for confirmation on reversible decisions.
- When a choice isn't specified, **pick the sensible default, proceed, and log it** in `DECISIONS.md`
  under "Assumptions". Do not ask.
- **Only stop to ask** when a choice is (a) **irreversible**, (b) **costs real money**, (c) a **safety/[DOMAIN]-critical**
  call only the owner can make, or (d) **conflicts** with this file or the KB.
- Never re-ask something already answered in `DECISIONS.md`.

## Do NOT ask about (assume the default)
- Folder structure, file naming, which ORM/validation lib — decided above.
- Formatting/lint style — [LINT_FORMAT_DEFAULTS, e.g. Prettier + ESLint defaults].
- Whether to write tests — **yes, always**, for logic and [CRITICAL_LOGIC_UNIT]s.
- Whether to add audit/tenant scope — **yes, always**.
- Minor library choices (date lib, uuid, etc.) — pick the standard one and log it.
- [ANY_OTHER_SETTLED_TOPIC].
